    "open_to_sit_in": true,
    "session_story": "London's longest-running free jazz jam, going strong for 25+ years. Alan Weekes — session credits include Art Blakey, Courtney Pine and Joss Stone — holds court every Sunday night from 8pm, often running past 3am. The house band anchors proceedings but the real magic is who drops in unannounced: Mark Kavuma, Ruben Fox and Cleveland Watkiss have all appeared. Clifford Jarvis, original drummer and Blue Note recording artist, was a founding member. Hackney's best-kept secret — Alan Weekes's own description.",
